Anyway, I too saw the exorcist when it was re-released in theatres a couple of years back. It was SO funny. Yeah, I wasn't afraid of it either. But thats to be expected. And now for my 2 cents. <br>
<br>
Of course, first I'll point out that the Exorcist first came out decades ago yadda yadda yadda. Now for the important stuff. Yes, there were subliminal messages in it, as was pointed out earlier by someone who's name I can't remember. But, all that stuff hasn't been in the movie for 25 years. Lemme just clear thing up.. The reason why people were so scared of the movie the first few weeks wasn't because the effects were new for their time, but because at the really frightening parts of the movie, the editors replaced individual frames of the movie with never before published Holocaust photographs. The audience didn't notice it with their eyes(duh), but their minds did... and that made them think that the movie was the scariest damn thing they've ever seen (keep in mind, these are HOLOCAUST photos). Then a couple of weeks later, the producrs were caught, the movie was put on the shelf for a while, the pictures were taken out and the movie was eventually put back into theatres, advertised as being &quot;scarier than ever before&quot;...which it wasn't...and is even less so today. The end. Wasn't that a great story? <p>&lt;b&gt;NieA loves you.&lt;/b&gt;</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wantsomepie>wantsomepie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(10/26/02 10:27:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11319.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.liquid2k.com/wantsomepie/animations/sloface.gif width=57 height=89></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: R</span><hr size=1> In response to Komikono[SPOILERS]<br>
